{"id":"094f4b5320b14ba889b74f84d6a0549d2dd3e946","axis":"silent","repo":"elastic/elasticsearch","sha":"094f4b5320b14ba889b74f84d6a0549d2dd3e946","parsed":{"files":[{"path":"docs/changelog/149713.yaml","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@","+area: TSDB","+issues: []","+pr: 149713","+summary: Add TO_GAUGE() function and ::gauge cast operator","+type: enhancement"],"additions":5,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/reference/query-languages/esql/_snippets/generated/x-pack-esql/functions/appendix/to_gauge.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@","+% This is generated by ESQL's ToGaugeTests. Do not edit it. See docs/reference/query-languages/esql/README.md for how to regenerate it.","+","+::::{warning}","+Applying `TO_GAUGE` to a field that is a genuine monotonically increasing counter, rather than a misclassified gauge, will produce raw cumulative counter values instead of gauge samples. Results from aggregations on such values are not meaningful.","+::::"],"additions":5,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/reference/query-languages/esql/_snippets/generated/x-pack-esql/functions/description/to_gauge.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@","+% This is generated by ESQL's ToGaugeTests. Do not edit it. See docs/reference/query-languages/esql/README.md for how to regenerate it.","+","+## Description","+","+Converts a counter value to its gauge (plain numeric) equivalent. The output type is determined by the input: `counter_long` converts to `long`, `counter_integer` to `integer`, and `counter_double` to `double`. No values are modified; only the type annotation changes. If the input is already a plain numeric or `aggregate_metric_double`, the function is a no-op. This is useful when a metric field was misclassified as a counter type instead of a plain numeric (gauge) in the index mapping. This function is also available as the `::gauge` cast operator.","+"],"additions":6,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/reference/query-languages/esql/_snippets/generated/x-pack-esql/functions/examples/to_gauge.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@","+% This is generated by ESQL's ToGaugeTests. Do not edit it. See docs/reference/query-languages/esql/README.md for how to regenerate it.","+","+## Example","+","+```esql","+TS k8s","+| STATS bytes_in = avg(avg_over_time(network.bytes_in::gauge)) BY cluster, time_bucket = bucket(@timestamp, 10minute)","+| EVAL bytes_in = round(bytes_in, 4)","+| KEEP bytes_in, cluster, time_bucket","+| SORT time_bucket, cluster","+| LIMIT 10;","+```","+","+| bytes_in:double | cluster:keyword | time_bucket:datetime |","+| --- | --- | --- |","+| 402.05 | prod | 2024-05-10T00:00:00.000Z |","+| 499.9387 | qa | 2024-05-10T00:00:00.000Z |","+| 497.1889 | staging | 2024-05-10T00:00:00.000Z |","+| 552.5219 | prod | 2024-05-10T00:10:00.000Z |","+| 495.0368 | qa | 2024-05-10T00:10:00.000Z |","+| 445.2519 | staging | 2024-05-10T00:10:00.000Z |","+| 718.6667 | prod | 2024-05-10T00:20:00.000Z |","+| 778.8333 | qa | 2024-05-10T00:20:00.000Z |","+| 400.4556 | staging | 2024-05-10T00:20:00.000Z |","+| ; |","+","+"],"additions":27,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/reference/query-languages/esql/_snippets/generated/x-pack-esql/functions/layout/to_gauge.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@","+% This is generated by ESQL's ToGaugeTests. Do not edit it. See docs/reference/query-languages/esql/README.md for how to regenerate it.","+","+```{applies_to}","+stack: ga 9.5.0","+```","+","+## Syntax","+","+:::{image} /reference/query-languages/esql/images/generated/x-pack-esql/functions/to_gauge.svg","+:alt: Embedded","+:class: text-center","+:::","+","+","+:::{include} ../parameters/to_gauge.md","+:::","+","+:::{include} ../description/to_gauge.md","+:::","+","+:::{include} ../types/to_gauge.md","+:::","+","+:::{include} ../examples/to_gauge.md","+:::","+","+:::{include} ../appendix/to_gauge.md","+:::"],"additions":28,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/reference/query-languages/esql/_snippets/generated/x-pack-esql/functions/parameters/t